What you need to know:

She said the contractor cannot dictate terms for the county government standing her ground that City Hall will not pay for the steel structure unless they are given the go ahead by the Public Procurement Regulatory Authority (PPRA) and Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC).“In professional terms, no one is able to pay for the steel structure until such a time we are guided by PPRA and EACC. This is the burden the contractor will have to carry,” said the Sports CEC.